RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 6F All Weather Track CR: 75. Waiver Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since February 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHILLY WILLY broke alertly, showed good early speed and set a pressured pace into the turn, carved out solid fractions while pressed to the quarter marker, shook free in upper stretch while holding foes at bay to the furlong marker, kept to task to the sixteenth-pole, felt late pressure from oncoming rivals, was fully extended in the final strides and dug in at the finish to prevail. COLONEL VARGO stalked the solid early pace, raced two wide between runners on the turn while advancing, shifted four wide for the drive, ran evenly to mid-stretch, rallied under steady left handed-urging to deep stretch, came within aim in the final strides and just missed for the win, while winning the nod for the place on the wire. FLY WICKED EAGLE chased the solid early pace, advanced three wide nearing the quarter marker, ran evenly while within aim to the furlong grounds, vied between runners in deep stretch, could not get by the determined winner in the final strides and was tagged for the place on the wire, while holding safely for the show. MR. FIGHTER forwardly placed in the early running, pressed the solid pace to the turn, kept close attendance to the pacesetter to the quarter marker, battled for the lead with CHILLY WILLY to mid-stretch, could not muster the needed response in deep stretch and weakened in the final sixteenth. WART chased the solid early pace from the inside, advanced on the turn, saved ground into upper stretch, angled three wide inside of the furlong marker and did not rally in the final stages. BIG STICK allowed to settle in the early running, raced outside of rivals into the turn, was coaxed five wide into the stretch and did not factor in the drive.

MORE POWER TO HIM prompted the moderate fractions while outside of POUR ON THE COLE, kept attendance to the pacesetter to the far turn, advanced in upper stretch and dueled with POUR ON THE COLE to deep stretch, took command at the sixteenth-marker, was overtaken by ECOLOGIST in the final strides and held for second at the finish. TWIRLING DERBY forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the moderate fractions while three wide into the backstretch run, lost a bit of ground heading to the second turn, raced three wide to the quarter marker, swung four wide for the drive, gained ground at mid-stretch, was outkicked in the final stages and was up in time to secure third. POUR ON THE COLE assumed command leaving the break, set moderate fractions while well rated through the backstretch run, showed the way to the quarter marker, was confronted in upper stretch by MORE POWER TO HIM, met that bid to the sixteenth-marker and weakened in deep stretch. SUNNY SPOT shuffled leaving the break and was off a bit slowly, was allowed to settle while not far back through the backstretch run, raced three wide into the second turn, came in a bit tight nearing the quarter marker, swung four wide for the drive, lost ground at mid-stretch, was gaining in the final furlong but could not muster the needed late response. WELLSWORT (IRE) allowed to settle early on, never far back through the backstretch run while outside of rivals, came four wide into the far turn, was coaxed five wide into the stretch, lost ground at the furlong pole and lacked a late rally.

FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE MARCH 15 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LORD WIMBORNE (IRE) allowed to settle early on, raced two wide into the backstretch run, maintained his position to the half-mile pole, advanced two wide on the second turn, mounted a four wide rally into the stretch, closed well to the furlong marker, battled with BROOKYS TAPIT to the sixteenth-pole, found more in deep stretch and edged away in the final strides to prevail. BROOKYS TAPIT settled off of the decent early pace, saved ground into the backstretch run, advanced three wide on the far turn, loomed in upper stretch, vied for the lead at the furlong marker, gained command inside of the furlong pole, battled with LORD WIMBORNE to the sixteenth-marker, relented in deep stretch and was outfinished for the win, while holding for the place. WALKING BOSS unhurried in the early running, was content to trail through the backstretch run, advanced two wide on the second turn, was roused five wide into the stretch, closed well to the furlong grounds, could not muster the needed response in deep stretch and was outkicked, while holding safely for third. SYNC allowed to settle in the early running, saved all of the ground to the second turn, was roused three wide into the stretch, was not able to reel in the leaders in the final stages but was gaining in deep stretch. ON RAGLAN ROAD tracked the decent early pace, raced two wide into the backstretch run, maintained his position to the half-mile marker, raced three wide into the second turn, advanced two wide at the quarter pole, battled with TIZONA to mid-stretch, took a narrow lead at the furlong marker, could not keep pace into deep stretch and weakened. TIZONA sent leaving the start and was prominent in the early running, stalked the decent pace along the first turn, came three then four wide into the backstretch run, dueled for the lead with DICK BEST through the backstretch run then assumed command heading to the far turn, came under pressure nearing the quarter pole, met the bid of ON RAGLAN ROAD and battled with that rival to the furlong marker, could not hold off oncoming rivals into the final furlong and faltered in the late stages. GORDY'S BOY took back in the early running, raced three wide into the backstretch run, advanced to track the pace to the half-mile pole, gained ground four then three wide on the second turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch and gave way in the final furlong. DICK BEST hustled leaving the break, set decent early fractions into the backstretch run, conceded the lead to TIZONA and stalked that rival to the half-mile marker, saved ground to the second turn, lost position nearing the quarter pole, re-rallied in upper stretch but could not sustain that run in the final stages and faded.
